<p>Why, in the console does this display the browser size after every size change (as expected):</p>  <pre><code>window.onresize = function() {         var width = $(window).width();           console.log(width); } </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://jsfiddle.net/5r35gLrc/" rel="nofollow">http://jsfiddle.net/5r35gLrc/</a></p>  <p>But when creating it as a function and calling it, it does not?:</p>  <pre><code>window.onresize = browserResizeAdjustments();  function browserResizeAdjustments() {     var width = $(window).width();       console.log(width);  } </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://jsfiddle.net/wxx8do60/" rel="nofollow">http://jsfiddle.net/wxx8do60/</a></p>  <p>The reason being is I want to run this onload as well, not just when the first browser size change happens.</p>  <p><strong>Final Solution:</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt; window.onresize = browserResizeAdjustments;  function browserResizeAdjustments() {     var width = $(window).width();       console.log(width);  }  // This runs it onload browserResizeAdjustments(); &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>